The pontiff, 85, said: "May there be peace for war-torn Ukraine, so sorely tried by the violence and destruction of this cruel and senseless war into which it was dragged." The pontiff, 85, said: "May there be peace for war-torn Ukraine, so sorely tried by the violence and destruction of this cruel and senseless war into which it was dragged." Square yesterday as he urged: "Please, please, let us not get used to war" and denounced "the flexing of muscles while people are suffering". He also cited "inhumane violence" in Libya and Yemen, "which suffers from a conflict forgotten by all".